# Synthetic secret test vectors — NOT real credentials.
#
# These files intentionally contain credential-shaped strings (a fake `ghp_`
# GitHub token, AWS's published `AKIAIOSFODNN7EXAMPLE` example key, etc.) so the
# scanner's own secret-detection, redaction, and MCP-audit tests have realistic
# inputs to detect. repomix's secretlint check flags them as a false positive
# and silently drops them from the pack. Excluding them here makes that
# intentional and explicit while keeping the security check useful (and
# un-noisy) for the rest of the repo. Nothing in these files is a real secret;
# there is nothing to rotate.
#
# Note: agentic-security does not itself use secretlint — it ships its own
# secret scanner (scanner/src/secrets/) plus a pre-commit bodyguard. This file
# only tunes the external `repomix` tool.
scanner/test/fixtures/mcp-audit/vuln-hardcoded-cred.mcp.json
scanner/test/mcp.test.js
